Financial appeal
On December 22, 2020, the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees and 30 humanitarian partners had appealed for USD156 million to meet "the critical humanitarian needs" of Ethiopian refugees fleeing the Tigray conflict through the first half of 2021.
The urgent financial appeal is also expected to strengthen the preparedness to receive refugees in other countries in the region in case of further movements, the UN refugee agency said.
Recalling the "colossal destruction" caused to infrastructure by the TPLF fighters, Demeke also emphasised the "daunting task" of reconstruction that is now underway with telecommunication lines being restored in almost all parts of the region and financial institutions resuming their operations.



